<BaseLayout
  title="Fellowships | US Fellows"
  description="Explore US Fellows programs and public-interest appointment pathways across science, civic life, education, Earth, innovation, and national capacity."
  canonical="https://usfellows.org/fellowships.html"
  activePage="fellowships"
>
  <main id="main">
<header class="page-hero"><div class="container"><div class="breadcrumbs"><a href="index.html">Home</a> / Fellowships</div><span class="kicker">Public-interest appointments</span><h1>A fellowship identity joined to meaningful contribution</h1><p>US Fellows appoints exceptional people to structured affiliations with mission-driven institutions, research efforts, civic projects, and public-benefit work.</p></div></header>
<nav class="anchor-nav" aria-label="On this page"><div class="container"><a href="#model">The Model</a><a href="#programs">Programs</a><a href="#scholars">R&amp;D Scholars</a><a href="#career">Career Advancement</a><a href="#international">International Graduates</a><a href="#national-capacity">National Capacity</a><a href="#appointments">Pathways</a></div></nav>
<section class="section" id="model"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro section-intro--center"><span class="eyebrow">The Fellowship Model</span><h2>Four elements define every appointment</h2><div class="rule"></div></div><div class="steps"><article class="step"><h3>The Fellow</h3><p>An individual selected for excellence, character, service, and mission alignment.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>The Mission</h3><p>A public-interest area of enduring and meaningful consequence.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>The Host</h3><p>A trusted institution that provides setting, supervision, and context.</p></article><article class="step"><h3>The Contribution</h3><p>A defined project, research effort, advisory role, or service commitment.</p></article></div></div></section>
<section class="section section--mist" id="programs"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">Fellowship Programs</span><h2>Distinct fields. A shared standard of service.</h2><div class="rule"></div></div><div class="program-grid"><article class="program"><LegacyIcon name="heart-o" /><h3>Humanity</h3><p>Human dignity, humanitarian work, public health, access, and flourishing.</p></article><article class="program"><LegacyIcon name="flask" /><h3>Science</h3><p>Inquiry, discovery, communication, technology, and evidence-based service.</p></article><article class="program"><LegacyIcon name="balance-scale" /><h3>Civic</h3><p>Public policy, trust, administration, legal access, and community resilience.</p></article><article class="program"><LegacyIcon name="book" /><h3>Education</h3><p>Learning, youth opportunity, mentorship, and human potential.</p></article><article class="program"><LegacyIcon name="leaf" /><h3>Earth</h3><p>Climate, conservation, biodiversity, justice, and planetary stewardship.</p></article><article class="program"><LegacyIcon name="lightbulb-o" /><h3>Innovation</h3><p>Public-benefit solutions from builders, designers, and technologists.</p></article><article class="program"><LegacyIcon name="graduation-cap" /><h3>International Graduate</h3><p>Field-aligned appointments for international graduates.</p></article><article class="program"><LegacyIcon name="shield" /><h3>National Capacity</h3><p>Resilience, infrastructure, systems, cybersecurity, and preparedness.</p></article><article class="program"><LegacyIcon name="compass" /><h3>Senior</h3><p>Strategic guidance from experienced leaders and domain experts.</p></article><article class="program"><LegacyIcon name="star" /><h3>Distinguished</h3><p>Exceptional accomplishment embodying the ideals of the Society.</p></article></div></div></section>
